    <cdata>
      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 169, Number 149 (Thursday, September 14, 2023)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Mr. EDWARDS:H.R. 5473.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8, Clause 3``Regulate commerce with foreign nations, and among theseveral states, and with the Indian tribes.''The single subject of this legislation is:Eliminates the sunset in the Disaster Recovery Reform Act(DRRA) to the definition of building codes to include thelast 2 cycles plus allowing for amendments, and updates thedefinition of building codes in Section 205 of the Robert T.Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act, Grantsto Entities for Establishment of Hazard Mitigation RevolvingLoan Funds.[Page H4347]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
